“hellfire.” Gehenna was the place outside of Jerusalem where fires were lit to dispose of rubbish by burning.
However, “hell” is a concept that is derived from Nordic and Anglo-Saxon mythology and does not parallel the
idea here. † 5:27 Quoting Exodus 20:14 or Deuteronomy 5:18. ‡ 5:31 Quoting Deuteronomy 24:1. § 5:33
