15 So then, what should I do? I will pray “in the Spirit,” but I will pray with my
mind too. I will sing “in the Spirit,” but I will sing with my mind too.§ 16 For if you
only pray “in the Spirit,” how can ordinary people that don't have understanding
say “Amen” after your prayer of thanks, since they haven't a clue what you said?
