alive; lashed, but not killed. 10 Seen as miserable, we are always rejoicing; as poor,
but we make many rich; as destitute, but we own everything!
11 I've been speaking bluntly, my Corinthian friends, loving you with a big heart!
12 We haven't kept our love from you, but you have kept your love from us. 13 Please
respond in the same way, as if you were my children, and be big-hearted!
14 Don't join together with people who don't believe—for what connection does
